Extremely disappointed... Arriving for a bowling game 1h45 before closing, we were informed that we could only play one and only one game, being 3 and 4 per lane, that is.... Realizing that our game ends and there is more than an hour before closing we kindly ask if it is possible to restart one on the track of three people, negative answer. By the time our part on the second track finished, so 10 or 15 minutes, the reception had let around ten people pass through. Obviously no justification for the fact that they can return and that we cannot play again. Between the flexible closure, not for us however and the fact that we are clearly paying for ourselves, I do not recommend. For the adventurous, plan to arrive at least two hours early for two bowling games. If you don't have that time, move on!
